I run 36mm Dells on a bus engine in a Beetle. 

Got 25 mpg pulling a Hyundai from VA to TN. 

My Porsche 911 Handbook (Bruce Anderson) carb sizing formula says 36mm (32mm venturis I think it was) is perfect for the VW aircooled VW 2.0L.

I recommend the BAS manifolds and linkage. www.ahnendorp.com

